*********************************************************************************
            IMPORTANT INSTALLATION INFORMATION
*********************************************************************************

1. Create a Drawer named "GQ2Demo" on any partition.
2. Extract the Archive GQ2Demo into the Drawer "GQ2Demo" you just created.
3. There  are four files that must remain in the drawer for the Demo to play:
 GQ2_Demo.AED, GQdemo.amin, AnimatEDPlay (AnimateED v1.52 by Marco Vigelius) and
 musix-shine.mod (from Amos PD CD - author unknown).
4. Additionaly, ensure you have the Pal Driver in the DEVS Monitor Drawer as the
 anim is set to play in Pal Low Res.

That's it. Double Click the "GQ_Demo.AED icon" and the demo animation will play. It
 is a little more than 4 minutes long giving you a sence of the adventure.

The animation should play on any amiga 1MB or higher, OS 2.0 or higher. The
 faster the  Amiga the better viewing experience of course.

